>
  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
    Voridus is arguably the best leader in Halo Wars 2 and one of the most unique. He's so good that he's banned in many tournaments. This guide covers an offensive opener build order focusing on Combat Spoils.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300">Combat Spoils - The Core Mechanic</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong class="text-cyan-400">What It Does:</strong> You get resources from damaging enemy buildings.
  </p>

  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong class="text-cyan-400">Key Detail:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Attack an <strong class="text-cyan-400">upgraded generator</strong> = you get <strong class="text-cyan-400">power</strong></li>
    <li>Attack anything else (harvesters, unupgraded generators, turrets, base, mini bases) = you get <strong class="text-cyan-400">supplies</strong></li>
  </ul>

  <p class="mb-4">Power is what you're really after to get a head start on tech progression.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Build Order: Chopper Harassment Opener</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">First Leader Point: Combat Spoils</h3>

  <p class="mb-4">Two main approaches for early aggression:</p>
  <ol class="list-decimal list-inside mb-6 ml-4 space-y-2">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Grunt Shrapnel Mines</strong> - Upgrade Grunts to Shrapnel Mines, send them to enemy base, use Y ability</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Mass Choppers</strong> (recommended) - Choppers fire frequently, generating lots of Combat Spoils income</li>
  </ol>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Why Choppers?</h3>

  <p class="mb-4">Choppers have terrible DPS but fire frequently. This means more Combat Spoils triggers. If you want to actually destroy generators, Grunts with Shrapnel Mines are better. For making money, Choppers are superior.</p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Early Game Execution</h3>

  <ol class="list-decimal list-inside mb-6 ml-4 space-y-2">
    <li>Collect resources with Grunts as usual</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Hold position Grunts on enemy mini bases</strong> - They'll attack when the enemy takes them, generating resources without you noticing</li>
    <li>Build Choppers and send them to harass enemy upgraded generators</li>
    <li>Your power income will skyrocket from Combat Spoils</li>
  </ol>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Important: Skip Shrapnel Rounds Upgrade</h3>

  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong class="text-cyan-400">Do NOT get Shrapnel Rounds</strong> for Choppers:
  </p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Costs 450 power (almost half of Tech 2 cost)</li>
    <li>Adds explosive rounds and detect</li>
    <li>You won't get a major return on investment even with constant generator harassment</li>
    <li>If you see opponents research this, they'll be stuck in their tech level for a while</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Second Leader Point Options</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">You really cannot go wrong with anything on Voridus's wheel:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Infusion Wake</strong> - Like a vortex that leaves damaging goo</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Grenadier Drop</strong> - Great against infantry, they explode and leave infusion goo</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Invigorating Frenzy</strong> - Only get if you have ways to create goo (Infused Engineers, Grenadier Drop)</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Infusion Tech</strong> - Increases infusion pool damage</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Mid-Game Transition</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">After Early Harassment</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Research Tech 2</li>
    <li>Build Foundry for Marauders</li>
    <li>Marauders cost no power - save power for tech and upgrades</li>
    <li>Can build Apex for Infused Engineers to support your army</li>
    <li>Add Choppers for fire rate to generate more Combat Spoils income</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Key Insight</h3>

  <p class="mb-4">You don't have to win every engagement against an opponent's base. Your advantage comes from the resources you generate every time you go on offense. This snowballs into a scary army composition early in the game.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Late Game Options</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Infusion Tech Path</h3>

  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong class="text-cyan-400">Infusion Tech 2</strong> is incredible:
  </p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Wraith Y ability (Scorch Mortar) creates infusion goo</li>
    <li>Blisterback shells create infusion goo</li>
    <li>Combined with other Voridus powers = most powerful siege in Halo Wars 2</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Team Combo: Maelstrom</h3>

  <p class="mb-4">If playing with allies, Maelstrom enables devastating combos:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Maelstrom + Beam</li>
    <li>Maelstrom + Eradication</li>
    <li>Maelstrom + Cryo Seismic</li>
    <li>The list goes on</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Cataclysm</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Ignites all infusion goo for massive explosion</li>
    <li>While Cataclysm is active, any new goo also explodes</li>
    <li>Drop Grenadier Drop, activate Infusion Wake, use Invigorating Frenzy while Cataclysm is active for massive damage</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong class="text-cyan-400">Note:</strong> Infusion goo does NOT damage bases directly. However, you CAN drop infusion goo on a base and use Cataclysm for serious damage.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Combat Spoils Level 2</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">Not recommended to upgrade. The increase in resources is nice, but Voridus's wheel is so good you should spend points elsewhere.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Voridus Hero</h2>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Similar behavior to Decimus's Warlord</li>
    <li>Y ability spreads infusion goo</li>
    <li>When fully upgraded, he becomes invisible in the goo</li>
    <li>Note: The hero levels out late game and doesn't become as dominant, but his leader wheel makes up for it</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">The Voridus Scarab</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">Voridus has the best Scarab in Halo Wars 2:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Main beam fires infusion goo</li>
    <li>Allows synergy with Cataclysm, Invigorating Frenzy, Infusion Tech</li>
    <li>Extra damage from goo effects</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Key Takeaways</h2>

  <ol class="list-decimal list-inside mb-6 ml-4 space-y-2">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Combat Spoils is incredible</strong> - Constant "cash back" at your opponent's expense</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Target upgraded generators</strong> for power income</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Choppers for fire rate</strong>, not DPS</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Skip Shrapnel Rounds</strong> - Too expensive for the return</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Everything on Voridus's wheel is great</strong> - You can't go wrong</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Keep the pressure on</strong> - You make money every time you attack</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Infusion Tech 2 + Blisterbacks</strong> = Best siege in the game</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Cataclysm</strong> ignites goo for massive burst damage</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Voridus Scarab</strong> is one of the best in the game</li>
  </ol>
